<para id="element-46">
<term>2: Acceleration is constant </term>
</para>
<para id="element-47">Constant acceleration means that instantaneous acceleration at all points during motion is same. It, therefore, implies that instantaneous acceleration at any time instant and average acceleration in any time interval during motion are equal.
</para>
<para id="element-48">
<m:math display="block">
<m:mtable columnalign="left">
<m:mtr>
<m:mtd>
<m:msub>
<m:mi> a </m:mi>
